<meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8">
</head>

<body>

<h1>@HI{{sa}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>


<p>
<ol>
<li>@Aistem{{}}<strong>@HI{{sa}}</strong>
<li>@Anastem{{}}<strong>@HI{{sa}}</strong>
</ol>
</dl>
</p>

<h2> Definition </h2>

Attaching the suffix @HI{{sa}} to the stem of an @HI{{i}}-adjective (or, much less commonly, to the stem of a @HI{{na}}-adjective)
makes a noun out of the adjective.
<p></p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

@HI{{kono uchi no}} @KJ{{wide}}<strong>@HI{{sa}}</strong> @HI{{ha choudo ii desu.}}

<h2> Notes </h2>

<h2> References </h2>

<p>
<ol>
<li> @REF{{MNN-TR-I}}. (Chapter 40)
<li> @REF{{DOBJG}}. (p381)
</ol>
</p>

